text.section:
The Commissioner may:
Designate one (1) or more areas of this state as elimination zones where boll weevil eradication programs will be undertaken;
Designate areas within the elimination zone where commercial and noncommercial cotton is prohibited from being planted;
Require all commercial cotton growers within an elimination zone to participate in a boll weevil eradication program; or
Destroy cotton being grown in prohibited areas of an elimination zone, and assess the grower for the costs incurred for the destruction.
